                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220220-50-off273 t18220220-50-crimeloc276"></join>. This box coat was in his house, it belongs to Mrs. Reeves, it was under my care - I drove her. It hung across the bannisters of Rutland's house - I came in with the carriage, on the 11th of February, a little past ten o'clock at night. I went home to No. 118, Jermyn-street; I have never seen the coat since.</p>
               <p>The Court ruled, that the indictment could not be sustained, as the coat was not Southgate's property, for being in Rutland's house, it was under his care.</p>
